The paper discusses the technical challenges of acquiring short-term credentials in Vehicular Communication (VC) systems, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also evaluates the system performance and privacy protection of different pseudonym acquisition policies, which involves system optimization (cs.SY) and data analysis (cs.DS). Finally, the paper leverages large-scale mobility datasets, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
